  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large pan, heat the butter and olive oil over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic cloves and cook for another minute, until fragrant.",
    "Meanwhile, prepare the aubergine by slicing them into 1/4-inch thick rounds.",
    "In a separate bowl, mix together the flour, milk, cottage cheese, chopped parsley, cheddar cheese, salt, black pepper, and breadcrumbs.",
    "Dip each aubergine slice into the mixture, coating both sides evenly.",
    "Place the coated aubergine slices in the prepared baking dish, overlapping them slightly.",
    "Drizzle with a little extra butter and sprinkle with paprika.",
    "Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the aubergine is tender and the top is golden brown."
  ],
